## Architecture Overview

### Dual-Process Model

FF Terminal employs a unique **dual-process architecture** that separates the AI runtime from the user interface:

1. **AI Daemon** (WebSocket server on port 28888)
   - Independent process that survives UI crashes
   - Handles all AI operations and tool execution
   - Manages sessions and conversation history
   - Supports autonomous operation for long-running tasks

2. **User Interface** (multiple options)
   - **Ink Terminal** - React-based terminal UI with real-time streaming
   - **Web Client** - Full-featured web interface (port 8787)
   - **FieldView Classic** - Terminal-aesthetic web interface (port 8788)

### Key Design Principles

| Principle | Implementation |
|-----------|---------------|
| **Crash Resilience** | Daemon runs independently; UI crashes don't lose session state |
| **Real-Time Communication** | WebSocket with delta encoding for streaming responses |
| **Thread Safety** | AsyncLocalStorage for context propagation across tool calls |
| **Session Continuity** | JSON-based conversation history with UUID session IDs |
| **Workspace Isolation** | Global vs local workspace modes with automatic port allocation |

### Communication Flow

```
User Input → UI (Ink/Web/FieldView)
           ↓ (WebSocket)
         Daemon (port 28888)
           ↓
         Agent Loop
           ↓ (tool calls)
         Tool Registry
           ↓ (execute)
         Tools/Skills
           ↓ (results)
         Agent Loop
           ↓ (streaming)
         Daemon
           ↓ (WebSocket)
         UI Display
```

### Component Responsibilities

| Component | Responsibility |
|-----------|---------------|
| **Ink Terminal** | Interactive CLI with color support, real-time streaming, keyboard shortcuts |
| **Web Client** | Full web UI with file upload, artifact preview, session management |
| **FieldView Classic** | Terminal-like web interface with smart scroll and mobile support |
| **WebSocket Server** | Bidirectional communication with delta encoding, auto-reconnect |
| **Agent Loop** | Multi-turn conversation management (max 500 turns per session) |
| **Provider Layer** | Abstraction for 6+ AI providers with unified API |
| **Tool Registry** | 35+ tools with OpenAI-style schemas, parallel execution support |
| **Skill System** | 40+ production skills across 8 categories |
| **Hooks System** | Plan validation, todo enforcement, skill restrictions |

